A vinification document moves through three statuses: **Processing**, **Released** and
**Closed**. Four actions on the Vinification card move it between these states.

```text
   Processing  ──Release──▶  Released  ──Close──▶  Closed
       ▲                        │                     │
       ├───Reopen released──────┘                     │
       │                                              │
       └──────────────Reopen closed───────────────────┘
```

All four actions are available in the **Release** split-button on the Vinification card and
are enabled only for the status they apply to.

## Release

**Available when:** Status = *Processing*.

Choose **Release** to post the consumption and output entries for all vinification phases.

What happens:

1. If output items require lot tracking, the [Lot Assignment](04-Lot-Assignment.md) window
   opens so you can distribute the output quantities across lot numbers.
2. The system creates the **wine treatment production orders** — one per relevant phase
   (vinification, fermentation, wine production, cellar surplus and, for white wines,
   coal treatment), using the reason codes from [Setup](02-Setup.md).
3. The document status changes to **Released** and the document becomes locked.

After release, the **Wine Treatments** section appears on the card.

## Reopen released

**Available when:** Status = *Released*.

Choose **Reopen released** to undo the release. The system reverses all posted entries and
deletes the wine treatment production orders, returning the status to **Processing** so you
can make corrections.

## Close

**Available when:** Status = *Released*.

Choose **Close** to finalise the vinification. The system verifies that **all** wine
treatment production orders have been posted. If so, the status changes to **Closed** and no
further modifications are allowed.

> If some treatments are not yet posted, closing is not allowed — post the outstanding
> treatments first.

## Reopen closed

**Available when:** Status = *Closed*.

Choose **Reopen closed** to revert a closed vinification. The system reverses all
consumption and output entries generated by the wine treatments, sets the wine treatment
production orders to **Finished** state, and the status returns to **Processing** so you
can make corrections.

## Wine Treatments section

Once a vinification is released, the **Wine Treatments** part shows the production orders in
a tree structure:

| Level | Shows |
|-------|-------|
| **Treatment** | The wine treatment (production order) for a phase, with its reason code and status. |
| **Prod. Order Line** | The production order line(s) under a treatment. |
| **Component** | The materials consumed and produced by the treatment. |

Displayed details include the **Production Order No.**, **Reason Code**, **Description**,
**Item No.**, quantities, unit of measure, location, due date and the
**Prod. Order Status**.

Use the **Wine Treatments** navigation action to open the full-page list, or the
**Wine Treatments** subform embedded on the card.

## Other navigation actions

| Action | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| **Statistics** (F7) | Opens the vinification statistics with total consumed and produced quantities from item ledger entries. |
| **Item Ledger Entries** | Shows all item ledger entries (consumption, output, transfers) generated by this vinification, for auditing and traceability. |
| **Wine Treatments** | Opens the wine treatment production orders created for this vinification and their posting status. |

## Posting wine treatments

The individual wine treatment production orders are posted using the standard EOS WINE
treatment posting pages. The Tracking Lines part on those pages shows the lot tracking
(Lot No. and Quantity Base) for full traceability. Once all treatments are posted you can
**Close** the vinification.